title: Well-lit Apartment w/ Updated Kitchen & Bathroom Near the Presidio!
posting_body: ['$2,695 | 133 19th Avenue #4, San Francisco, CA 94121', 'This spacious and light filled one-bedroom apartment is centrally located where Central Richmond and Sea Cliff meet.', ' Just a few short blocks from all the shops, restaurants and nightlife that California and Clement Street have to offer and one block from the Presidio.', 'This residence boasts gorgeous hardwood floors throughout, updated eat-in kitchen, ample closet space and light filled living room with large bay windows.', 'This apartment radiates San Francisco Charm!', 'Walk Score: 94 (Walkers Paradise)', 'KEY FEATURES:', '- Updated eat-in kitchen', '- Gorgeous hardwood floors throughout', '-Windows to let in great natural light', '- Ample closet space', '- Kitchen w/ gas stove & refrigerator', '-Update bathroom w/ shower over tub', 'TERMS:', '1 year lease', 'Security Deposit = 1 month + $500', 'No smoking', 'Water & Garbage Included; tenants pay PG&E', 'Sorry, no pets!', 'Available now!', 'Contact Brett for more information or to schedule a tour!', 'Online application available upon request.', 'Brett van den Eikhof', 'DRE #01910306', 'brett@gaetanirealestate <URL>)', 'For more units available, visit <URL>', 'This unit is a rental unit subject to the San Francisco Rent Ordinance, which limits evictions without just cause, and which states that any waiver by tenant of their rights under the rent ordinance is void as contrary to public policy.']
